Noddy, Big Ears, Mr. Plod, and several other characters from\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children%27s_literature#United_Kingdom"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 British children's literature}}\'a0appeared at the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children%27s_Party_at_the_Palace"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Children's Party at the Palace}}\'a0on 25 June 2006 in honour of the 80th birthday of\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_II"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 Queen Elizabeth II}}. During the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pantomime"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 pantomime}}-style play called\'a0
